This paper deals with model compression of ConvNets, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the trade-off between accuracy and speed, which is a common concern in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the proposed algorithm involves ranking and pruning filters, which is a technique commonly used in data structures (cs.DS).
